      "Liberia's total merchandise exports reached US$2,068.21 million in 2025, up 57.9 percent from US$1,309.82 million in 2024, according to Central Bank of Liberia data. It is the first time the country has crossed the US$2 billion export threshold.",
      "The surge was driven almost entirely by one destination. Exports to Europe and Oceania totaled US$1,688.1 million, accounting for 81.6 percent of all goods sold abroad. That is up 45.68 percent from US$1,158.78 million in 2024, and it represents a remarkable concentration: more than four out of every five dollars Liberia earns from exports now flow from a single regional market.",
      "The European dominance reflects the commodity mix. Gold, which has overtaken iron ore as Liberia's top export, is overwhelmingly routed to Swiss refineries. Iron ore moves to European steelmakers. Rubber goes to European tire manufacturers. The destination is determined by the buyer, not by Liberian exporters — most of whom are multinational concessionaires, not locally owned trading firms.",
