      "The mining sector's weight in the economy has shifted dramatically. Mining and panning generated US$710.82 million in constant-price GDP in 2025, up 5.98 percent from US$670.7 million in 2024 and representing 18.4 percent of real GDP. Five years ago, the figure was about 8 percent. The sector is now the second-largest contributor to real output after agriculture.",
