    summary: "Exports to China surged to US$134.19 million in 2025 from just US$0.61 million the year before — a jump so large it reshaped Liberia's trade geography overnight. The recovery echoes the US$146.26 million China bought in 2014 at the peak of the last iron-ore cycle, and it signals that a major commodity channel has reopened.",
