    summary: "With personal loan rates at 16.16%, commercial lending at 13.11%, and bank credit to the private sector growing just 1.1% year-on-year, Liberia's startup environment is defined by the cost and scarcity of capital. The economy is growing at 4.57% in real terms — but the barriers to turning that growth into new businesses remain steep.",
