      "Liberia produced 37,834.6 ounces of gold in March 2026, up 14.96 percent from 32,911.7 ounces a year earlier, according to data from the Liberia Institute of Statistics and Geo-Information Services. The figure sits close to the 24-month average of about 38,166 ounces per month — a level of output that has been broadly stable since mid-2024, even as individual months swing widely.",
